# Use case: Print the characters which are present at an even index of a string..

Accept string from a user and display only those characters which are present at an even index number.

str = "Its a wonderful day"
for i in range(0,len(str)-1, 2):
    print("index[",i,"]", str[i])

Output:
index[ 0 ] I
index[ 2 ] s
index[ 4 ] a
index[ 6 ] w
index[ 8 ] n
index[ 10 ] e
index[ 12 ] f
index[ 14 ] l
index[ 16 ] d
